QUESTION 5728455bff5b5019007da07b = How much Saharan dust remains in the air over the Amazon each year?
   
TEXT 5728455bff5b5019007da07b = NASA's CALIPSO satellite has measured the amount of dust transported by wind from the Sahara to the Amazon: an average 182 million tons of dust are windblown out of the Sahara each year, at 15 degrees west longitude, across 1,600 miles (2,600 km) over the Atlantic Ocean (some dust falls into the Atlantic), then at 35 degrees West longitude at the eastern coast of South America, 27.7 million tons (15%) of dust fall over the Amazon basin, 132 million tons of dust remain in the air, 43 million tons of dust are windblown and falls on the Caribbean Sea, past 75 degrees west longitude.
   
ANSWERS 5728455bff5b5019007da07b = {'132 million tons'}

QUESTION 5729ea263f37b319004785c0 = How many miles across the Atlantic Ocean does Saharan dust travel?
   
TEXT 5729ea263f37b319004785c0 = NASA's CALIPSO satellite has measured the amount of dust transported by wind from the Sahara to the Amazon: an average 182 million tons of dust are windblown out of the Sahara each year, at 15 degrees west longitude, across 1,600 miles (2,600 km) over the Atlantic Ocean (some dust falls into the Atlantic), then at 35 degrees West longitude at the eastern coast of South America, 27.7 million tons (15%) of dust fall over the Amazon basin, 132 million tons of dust remain in the air, 43 million tons of dust are windblown and falls on the Caribbean Sea, past 75 degrees west longitude.
   
ANSWERS 5729ea263f37b319004785c0 = {'1600', '1600 miles'}

QUESTION 572749d7dd62a815002e9a92 = How many seasons did The Love Boat run for?
   
TEXT 572749d7dd62a815002e9a92 = For its part, the television network produced a few new hits during 1977: January saw the premiere of Roots, a miniseries based on an Alex Haley novel that was published the previous year; in September, The Love Boat, a comedy-drama anthology series produced by Aaron Spelling which was based around the crew of a cruise ship and featured three stories centered partly on the ship's various passengers; although critically lambasted, the series turned out to be a ratings success and lasted nine seasons.
